text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia ingramii is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae that is native to parts of north eastern Australia.
The shrub or tree typically grows to a height of 2 to 5 m (6 ft 7 in to 16 ft 5 in) and has a spreading bushy habit.
The shrub has a limited distribution in upper basin of the Macleay River in New South Wales to the east of Armidale.
